---
description: Frontend architecture boundaries for apps/web and modules
alwaysApply: true
---

# Frontend Architecture

- `apps/web` is the composition layer for routes, layouts, and page assembly.
- Business logic should be implemented in `modules/<module-name>/`, not directly in page files.
- Keep page files thin: they should call module APIs/hooks/components and render.
- Module code should be organized by feature ownership, not by route ownership.
- Shared app-shell concerns (providers, global layout, metadata, navigation) can stay in `apps/web`.

# Import Direction

- Allowed: `apps/web` imports from `modules/*`.
- Avoid importing route-specific code back into modules.
- Keep module APIs explicit through module-level exports to reduce deep relative imports.

# Module Boundaries

- Each module owns its own internal logic and data access flows.
- Prefer extending an existing module over scattering related logic in multiple routes.
